  "location": "Private GP clinic, Tuen Mun",
  "context": "Most Hong Kongers see private GPs (私家醫生) for minor illness — it's quick and affordable compared to public hospitals. Clinics are usually in the ground floor of residential blocks. Register at reception, wait your turn, then see the doctor for 5-10 minutes.",
  "cultural_note": "Before going to a pharmacy or clinic, many Hongkongers visit a 涼茶舖 (leong4 caa4 pou3, herbal tea shop). These small shops have existed on HK street corners since the 1800s, selling medicinal teas brewed from Chinese herbs to treat 熱氣 (jit6 hei3, \"hot energy\"), the internal imbalance Cantonese medicine attributes to fried food, late nights, and stress. It's the first line of defence.",
